Body: After installing or updating an app in the newest version of the android market I receive the warning "Process System is not responding" with the option to either force close or wait. I choose "wait" and everything continues as normal. It's not a major issue just a mild annoyance, also it interferes with automatic updates.I have tried fixing permissions, wiping dalvik cache, etc. but to no avail.Has anyone else seen this issue? I have googled this problem but haven't found too many relevant threads. Title: App installs result in "Process System Not Responding" message

history.Text: After installing or updating an app in the newest version of the android market I receive the warning "Process System is not responding" with the option to either force close or wait. I choose "wait" and everything continues as normal. It's not a major issue just a mild annoyance, also it interferes with automatic updates. I have tried fixing permissions, wiping dalvik cache, etc. but to no avail.Has anyone else seen this issue? I have googled this problem but haven't found too many relevant threads. I am running CM 7.1.0 android version 2.3.7 with Tiamat kernel 4.1.0.
